        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 25 at 5:13PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 512 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Timber Butte, or 15 miles east of Jackpot, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Timber Butte around 520 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
